      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRANKENSTEINSBRIDE (2) was successful at her most recent outing by 7 metres in a nice return to form at Gloucester Park over 1730m. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Her recent effort is good enough to take out a race like this. YA BETTOR FOLLOWME (7) was out of the money two starts ago then things went wrong last start when he broke and finished a distant tenth over 2560m at Northam. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Finds a nice race and can make amends. BOLD JACKIE (1) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 2190m at Northam. Should run a big race. MAJIC BAY (9) is worth another chance after a last-start seventh over 2180m at Wagin three-and-a-half weeks ago.",
